The metapodials are relatively long and slender (
Fig. 26
). The index Length McIII × 100/Length radius is 75.5 indicating a relatively long metacarpal. The robusticity index (m11 × 100/m1) is 16.0 for McIII and 14.3 for MtIII respectively, indicating long and relatively robust metapodials. The facet for cuneiforme II is always present. The keel index (m12 × 100/m13) is 120.4 for McIII and 128.4 for MtIII, indicating a well developed keel. COMPARISONS
